*create table syntax-
CREATE TABLE <table-name> ( <column-list> [<constraint-list>] )

*Example- CREATE TABLE corporation
 (corp_id SMALLINT,
  name VARCHAR(30),
  CONSTRAINT pk_corporation PRIMARY KEY (corp_id)
 );

* CONSTRAINT and its syntax

 1) CONSTRAINT PKCourse PRIMARY KEY(CourseNo)
 
 2) CONSTRAINT PKEnrollment PRIMARY KEY (OfferNo, StdNo)
 
 3) CONSTRAINT UniqueCrsDesc UNIQUE (CrsDesc)
 
 4) CONSTRAINT FKOfferNo FOREIGN KEY (OfferNo) REFERENCES Offering
 
 5) CONSTRAINT OffCourseNoReq NOT NULL
 
 *Types of CONSTRAINT
   1 inline 
   2 external
   
   inline eg- CREATE TABLE employee (
              emp_id NUMBER(10) PRIMARY KEY,
              first_name VARCHAR2(200),
              last_name VARCHAR2(200),
              dept_id NUMBER(10) FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES department);
              
   External eg - CREATE TABLE employee (
              emp_id NUMBER(10) ,
              first_name VARCHAR2(200),
              last_name VARCHAR2(200),
              dept_id NUMBER(10)  
              CONSTRAINT empid PRIMARY KEY(emp_id),
              CONSTRAINT deptid FOREIGN KEY(dept_id) REFERENCES department);
              
              
   *Check Constraint 
   -used to check the constaints of colums
   -use check keyword here 
   
   Examples 
   1) CONSTRAINT ValidGPA 
      CHECK ( StdGPA BETWEEN 0 AND 4 )

   2) CONSTRAINT ValidStdClass 
      CHECK ( StdClass IN ('FR','SO', 'JR', 'SR' )

   3) CONSTRAINT OffYearValid 
      CHECK ( OffYear > 1970 )




         
   
              
              
              
              
